use strict;
use warnings;
#
use App::bsky::CLI;
exit App::bsky::CLI->new->run(@ARGV);

__END__

=encoding utf-8

=head1 NAME

bsky - A Command-line Bluesky Client

=head1 SYNOPSIS

    # create user session
    $ bsky login [handle] [password]

    # view recent posts
    $ bsky timeline

    # create a post
    $ post

=head1 DESCRIPTION

C<bsky> is a simple command line client for Bluesky in Perl.

=head1 Usage

   bsky [global options] command [command options] [arguments...]

=head2 Commands

=over

=item C<show-profile>

show profile

=item C<update-profile>

update profile

=item C<timeline>, C<tl>

show timeline

=item C<thread>

show thread

=item C<post>

post new text

=item C<vote>

vote the post

=item C<votes>

show votes of the post

=item C<repost>

repost the post

=item C<reposts>

show reposts of the post

=item C<follow>

follow the handle

=item C<follows>

show follows

=item C<followers>

show followers

=item C<delete>

delete the note

=item C<login>

login the social

=item C<help>, C<h>

shows a list of commands or help for one command

=back

=head2 Global Options

=over

   -a value       profile name
   -V             verbose (default: false)
   --help, -h     show help
   --version, -v  print the version

=back

=head1 See Also

L<At>.pm

L<https://github.com/mattn/bsky> - Original Golang client

